# Skin Care Module — Implementation Plan

## Goal

Build a full-featured Skin Care module that lets users:
1. **Onboard** by selecting their current skincare products (allopathic / homeopathic categories)
2. **Get an AI-generated daily skincare plan** with a duration (days/months/years)
3. **View today's routine** as a checklist they can mark done
4. **Update their products** anytime → triggers a new AI plan
5. **See a calendar view** of the past month showing completion status per day
6. **Retroactively update** any past day (e.g., mark yesterday's tasks complete today)

---

## Proposed Changes

### Backend — Mongoose Model

#### [NEW] [SkinCarePlan.js](file:///c:/Users/Dell/Desktop/Mini%20Project/Code/backend/models/SkinCarePlan.js)

Stores the user's selected products, the AI-generated plan, and daily task logs.

```js
// Key fields:
{
  user: ObjectId (ref User),
  products: [{ name, type: "allopathic"|"homeopathic", category: "cleanser"|"toner"|... }],
  plan: {
    routine: {
      morning: [{ step, product, instruction, duration }],
      night:   [{ step, product, instruction, duration }]
    },
    followFor: String,         // e.g. "30 days", "3 months"
    tips: [String],
    generatedAt: Date
  },
  dailyLogs: [{
    date: String ("YYYY-MM-DD"),
    morningCompleted: [Boolean],  // one per morning step
    nightCompleted: [Boolean],    // one per night step
    notes: String
  }]
}
```

One document per user (upserted). The `dailyLogs` array holds up to ~30–60 entries.

---

### Backend — Routes

#### [NEW] [skinCareRoutes.js](file:///c:/Users/Dell/Desktop/Mini%20Project/Code/backend/routes/skinCareRoutes.js)

| Endpoint | Method | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| `/api/skincare/plan` | `GET` | Get user's current plan + products |
| `/api/skincare/plan` | `POST` | Save selected products → call Gemini AI → store generated plan |
| `/api/skincare/log` | `POST` | Log/update daily task completion (any date, allows retroactive) |
| `/api/skincare/log/:date` | `GET` | Get log for a specific date |
| `/api/skincare/calendar` | `GET` | Get all daily logs for calendar view (last 31 days) |

AI plan generation uses the **Gemini API** (already available via `@google/generative-ai` in the backend, same pattern as chatbot which uses Groq). Will use Gemini directly in the route (same as [aiRoutes.js](file:///c:/Users/Dell/Desktop/Mini%20Project/Code/backend/routes/aiRoutes.js) pattern) rather than proxying to FastAPI, since this is a one-shot generation, not a multi-step graph.

#### [MODIFY] [index.js](file:///c:/Users/Dell/Desktop/Mini%20Project/Code/backend/index.js)

Add: `import skinCareRoutes` and `app.use("/api", skinCareRoutes);`

